snippet.textDisplay:
I would love love love to win this giveaway because there are people in my life who deserve luxurious gifts that I can’t afford to give them. I never would have thought to give them make up or skin care because I was never really into that until I started watching you, Tati. I came across your channel when I was looking up how magnetic eyelashes work (since I thought it would make my morning routine faster) and I found your review. I immediately fell in love with your channel because you are committed to 1) lifting up and supporting other make up artists and 2) recommending products that are affordable and reliable.

As a first year teacher, I am spending an insane amount of money on my classroom. My classroom came with some furniture and materials, but everything else, I am buying with my own money. I am happy doing it because my students live in extreme poverty and some live in crisis situations at home, so they deserve a welcoming environment with tons of resources and love to go around. I truly believe it is a good use of my money.

The only problem is… I don’t have a lot of money left over for myself and the people I love. This Christmas, I am struggling to afford presents for people who have helped me set up my classroom, who have stayed up late cutting and laminating numbers and letters for my students, who have spent their OWN money on MY students. I have such an amazing support system (which I believe every teacher needs) and I really want to thank them for all of the sacrifices they’ve made so that I and my students can be a successful. 

Receiving this giveaway means I can give beautiful make up to my best friend who helped me set up my bulletin board and organized supplies on a Friday night. It means I can give my boyfriend, who has built my desk, book shelves and chairs for my classroom, skin care and sunscreen to protect his annoyingly perfect skin (which he does nothing to take care of). It means I can give my dad nourishing skin care products for coming straight to my classroom from the airport to help me set up (which would be amazing because he has squamous cells carcinomas - a cancer on the surface of your skin that has to be burned off over and over again). It means I can give my mom brand new, trending make up (since she’s been using the same dated products for 30 years) for spending so so so much of her hard-earned money on my classroom AND for tutoring my most at-risk students. And it means I can spend time on myself using these beautiful products. I pour so much of my time and energy into my students and I love to do it, but I also know that I am wearing thin. It is important for me to learn that taking care of myself is taking care of my students because they need a well-rested and energized teacher. These products could help me do that. They can help me spend a little extra time on myself in the morning before work and a little extra time on myself before getting ready for bed.

I love love love you, Tati. You’re the only account I am subscribed to because you’re the only channel that brings me joy! Your kindness and generosity is contagious and I can’t wait to continue spreading it in my classroom.

My three greatest passions are hiking, photography, and all things makeup. Growing up, I was a part of various sports teams. I struggled a lot with being athletic, but also wanting to look my best while doing so, and got teased for wearing makeup to volleyball practice, or big track meet days. I tried fitting in with wearing no makeup at all, but I simply hated it! Why was I letting others determine what to do with my face?? So I started learning about more natural applications, ways to make makeup stay longer and through sweat, and how proper skincare minimizes makeup products you need to use. I loved learning about the ingredients of everything I was putting on my skin, and I quickly became obsessed with finding the best products out there.

It would be so freakin cool to win this giveaway and dive extensively into each brand and its products, and share important findings with others to make the best and healthiest choices they can. It’s crazy how much makeup has lead me to living a healthier lifestyle, and I hope others who have a budding passion aren’t deterred by those who see makeup as pointless, silly, or even purely provocative! You can be sporty, you can be smart, and you can be anything with a full face of your favorites on. :)
